HEADWORD: Clerisy
<hw>Cler"i*sy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>clericia</ets>. See <er>Clergy</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
literati, or well educated class.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The clergy, or their opinions, as opposed to the
laity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

